in slow motion.

140
00:08:29,802 --> 00:08:32,096
Shi...ni...ga...mi, huh?

141
00:08:32,304 --> 00:08:33,347
But...

142
00:08:34,056 --> 00:08:36,017
<i>He seems to have reacted
to the scrap of paper at his feet.</i>

143
00:08:37,309 --> 00:08:38,477
He just gave a small sigh.

144
00:08:39,645 --> 00:08:43,607
<i>He talks a bit more here.
I'll zoom in on his mouth.</i>

145
00:08:46,527 --> 00:08:49,572
That...Shi...ni...ga...mi...

146
00:08:50,197 --> 00:08:55,161
Just. . .gave. . .me. ..
the. . .note. . .book...

147
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:59,498
And. . .hasn't. . .appeared. . .since...

148
00:09:04,170 --> 00:09:06,922
"That Shinigami just
gave me the notebook...

149
00:09:07,006 --> 00:09:08,632
"and hasn't appeared since. .

150
00:09:12,011 --> 00:09:15,014
Mikami was given the notebook
by a Shinigami.

151
00:09:15,139 --> 00:09:18,726
But the Shinigami hasn't
been following him.

152
00:09:23,064 --> 00:09:24,273
I see...

153
00:09:28,569 --> 00:09:30,988
Then I guess that'll be it for today...

154
00:09:31,697 --> 00:09:32,782
Yeah...

155
00:09:35,493 --> 00:09:36,827
It's finally over.

156
00:09:37,244 --> 00:09:38,996
Today was really quite amazing.

157
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:41,499
It's tough to do this for several hours.

158
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:43,709
But you're still smiling.

159
00:09:44,794 --> 00:09:46,796
Then I'll go to the hotel and checkout.

160
00:09:47,838 --> 00:09:49,006
Thanks for your help!

161
00:09:49,715 --> 00:09:50,966
Must be tough for Aizawa,

162
00:09:51,050 --> 00:09:54,053
making all the reservations
and checking out of the hotels.

163
00:10:20,621 --> 00:10:23,749
<i>It's gone... The mark I made
with my nail is gone!</i>

164
00:10:33,634 --> 00:10:36,220
<i>Two of the four marks
I left are gone...</i>

165
00:10:37,429 --> 00:10:38,639
<i>The room is the way they left it.</i>

166
00:10:39,932 --> 00:10:41,684
<i>The hotel staff hasn't come in yet...</i>

167
00:10:42,601 --> 00:10:46,397
<i>So why has the notepad
been switched with a new one .7</i>

168
00:10:48,774 --> 00:10:50,985
<i>They're. . . passing notes!</i>

169
00:10:56,448 --> 00:10:57,491
Yes?

170
00:11:00,119 --> 00:11:03,622
What? You want to meet and talk
to Near directly?

171
00:11:11,130 --> 00:11:13,757
Mr. Aizawa, it's been a while.

172
00:11:14,508 --> 00:11:16,093
And also. . .nice to meet you.

173
00:11:16,802 --> 00:11:19,972
There's no point in saying that
if I'm blindfolded.

174
00:11:20,806 --> 00:11:22,892
He doesn't have any weapons
or cameras on him.

175
00:11:23,642 --> 00:11:26,103
Then you can take off the blindfold.

176
00:11:33,319 --> 00:11:36,322
Near, I believe you.

177
00:11:37,364 --> 00:11:39,617
I and Takada are meeting
almost every night.

178
00:11:40,242 --> 00:11:41,243
I know.

179
00:11:42,620 --> 00:11:43,787
Then what about this?

180
00:11:44,038 --> 00:11:46,332
There's no mistake that
they're passing notes!

181
00:11:47,583 --> 00:11:51,587
Mr. Aizawa, please don't do
anything unnecessary.

182
00:11:52,379 --> 00:11:53,380
"Do anything unnecessary?"

183
00:11:54,256 --> 00:11:56,300
Yes. It's no longer a matter

184
00:11:56,425 --> 00:11:59,470
of simply finding
evidence against Kira.

185
00:12:00,137 --> 00:12:05,476
We must hit Kira with complete defeat
in order to stop him.

186
00:12:06,644 --> 00:12:08,979
Mr. Aizawa, I'll say this bluntly.

187
00:12:09,438 --> 00:12:12,316
You and the task force are
no longer a part of this battle.

188
00:12:15,152 --> 00:12:18,197
But if you still want
to capture Kira,

189
00:12:18,781 --> 00:12:21,742
just keep an eye on him,
as you've been doing.

190
00:12:22,493 --> 00:12:23,994
Just keep an eye on him?

191
00:12:24,787 --> 00:12:28,832
Yes. But there is a purpose
to keeping watch over L.

192
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:32,795
And that's part of my plan.

193
00:12:33,504 --> 00:12:36,840
I want you to cooperate that way.

194
00:12:37,883 --> 00:12:39,301
In order to win against Kira...

195
00:12:40,386 --> 00:12:41,845
And watch...

196
00:12:43,973 --> 00:12:45,224
the end of Kira.

197
00:13:01,615 --> 00:13:04,910
<i>There's only a few minutes
left of this year,</i>

198
00:13:05,035 --> 00:13:08,038
<i>one that's been one full of
breakthroughs for me.</i>

199
00:13:08,038 --> 00:13:11,750
EAST-WEST POP FESTIVAL

200
00:13:12,334 --> 00:13:16,463
<i>I'm Kiyomi Takada, your host.
Thank you very much for everything.</i>

201
00:13:17,464 --> 00:13:19,675
The Pop Song Festival is
about to begin!

202
00:13:20,259 --> 00:13:23,470
Matsuda, have you crosschecked
the Kira murders and the victims?

203
00:13:23,929 --> 00:13:28,976
After Misa-Misa's performance!
She's this year's opening act!

204
00:13:34,606 --> 00:13:36,066
W-What is it. . .?

205
00:13:40,112 --> 00:13:41,280
We're the SPK...

206
00:13:42,114 --> 00:13:43,449
We want you to come with us.

207
00:13:47,119 --> 00:13:50,873
<i>I must apologize to everyone.</i>

208
00:13:51,749 --> 00:13:57,588
<i>Unfortunately, this year's opener,
Misa Amane, has not arrived yet.</i>

209
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:00,507
<i>However...</i>

210
00:14:00,591 --> 00:14:02,301
- <i>What's</i> going <i>on?</i>
- <i>unexpected things can happen...</i>

211
00:14:02,718 --> 00:14:04,678
- Mogi didn't tell me anything about this.
- at' the Pop Song <i>F</i> est/val.

212
00:14:07,139 --> 00:14:09,808
Go back to NHN immediately!

213
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:14,355
I'm already known as the queen
of last-minute cancellations!

214
00:14:14,646 --> 00:14:17,107
Misa-Misa, stay calm.

215
00:14:17,649 --> 00:14:18,942
Mochi, why?!

216
00:14:19,485 --> 00:14:21,028
We need to do this to catch Kira.

217
00:14:21,111 --> 00:14:23,655
That doesn't involve me!

218
00:14:23,864 --> 00:14:27,159
If worse came to worst,
I was prepared to pull a gun on you...

219
00:14:27,326 --> 00:14:31,372
But I'm glad that
you didn't resist, Mr. Mogi.

220
00:14:33,749 --> 00:14:37,044
<i>I probably would have resisted if
I hadn't listened to what Aizawa said...</i>

221
00:14:37,169 --> 00:14:41,799
<i>But hearing about the notepad,
there's no doubt that...</i>

222
00:14:44,802 --> 00:14:45,928
What's going on?

223
00:14:47,638 --> 00:14:48,722
Near.

224
00:14:48,806 --> 00:14:50,265
<i>What is it, L?</i>

225
00:14:50,849 --> 00:14:53,268
Mogi and Misa Amane
have gone missing.

226
00:14:53,936 --> 00:14:57,439
<i>Yes. I've taken them
into my custody.</i>

227
00:14:58,023 --> 00:14:59,108
What for?!

228
00:14:59,316 --> 00:15:00,401
Why?

229
00:15:01,402 --> 00:15:02,820
